<title>MEXICO: Banco de Mexico to drain 1.879 bln pesos.</title>
<headline>Banco de Mexico to drain 1.879 bln pesos.</headline>
<dateline>MEXICO CITY 1997-05-12</dateline>
<text>
<p>Banco de Mexico sought to drain 1.879 billion pesos from the secondary market on Monday through a combination of three direct sales of paper and five repurchase agreements, dealers said.</p>
<p>The Cetes sales were offered as follows:</p>
<p>    AMOUNT     TERM</p>
<p>    150 million    360 days</p>
<p>    150 million    178 days</p>
<p>    150 million     87 days</p>
<p>The terms and maturities of the repurchase agreements were offered as follows:</p>
<p>    400 million     39 days</p>
<p>    300 million     25 days</p>
<p>    300 million     16 days</p>
<p>    250 million     10 days</p>
<p>    179 million	1 day</p>
<p>*Amounts in pesos</p>
<p>(( --Mexico City newsroom +525 728-9559))</p>
